{"questionId":"33028781","questionHtml":"<p>Sketch the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> on the following grid.<br><br><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/81c72ff31695ba5acb64394faa2272fe20d96cb4.png\" width=\"441\" height=\"339\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/32861ced95b3f65c055e8ded0826aa5912a046cb.png\" width=\"442\" height=\"349\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>A1A1A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>Note</strong>: Follow through from their part (a).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Award <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for endpoints at approximately&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo></math>. Allow for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-intercept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn></math> and for the right endpoint in the interval <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The following two <em><strong>A</strong></em> marks may only be awarded if the approximate shape is correct.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercepts at approximately <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;and award <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for maximum at approximately <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math>. Allow for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercepts in the intervals <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>18</mn></math>, and maximum in the intervals <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33028781","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.1c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Sketch the graph of y=f(x) on the following grid.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}